NIMO says restarting 610 MW N . Y . nuke Wed . Niagara Mohawk Power Corp ( NIMO ) said Wednesday it plans to restart its 610 megawatt ( MW ) Nine Mile Point 1 nuclear power station later today . " We ' re on schedule to start up later today . It usually takes about 24 hours before it goes on line , " said company spokesman Alberto Bianchetti . The unit shut down Aug 18 to repair a feedwater pump , he said . Feedwater pump problems have been interrupting operation of the plant since Aug 8 . Nine Mile Point produces about three percent of NIMO ' s electricity deliveries . The utility provides power to about 1 . 5 million customers in upstate New York . - - New York Power Desk + 1 212 859 1628 
